Practical:09  Aim: To study database programming using SQLite in Android. 
Problem Statement:Develop an Android application using SQLite database to create a table and perform insert, update, delete and display operations on the stored records. 

What is SQLite? SQLite is a lightweight database built inside Android. 
      No installation needed 
      No internet required 
      Works offline 
      Data stored inside app 
      
What We Will Build 
A simple Student Record App 
Table: student 
Columns: id (Primary Key), name, marks 
Operations: Insert student Update student Delete student Display all students 

